        "Add all the digits of that number",
        "Keep adding until you get a single digit",
        "The answer will ALWAYS be 9!"
      ],
      "example": "Is 171 a multiple of 9?\n→ Add digits: 1+7+1 = 9\n→ YES! It is a multiple of 9!\n\nIs 254 a multiple of 9?\n→ Add digits: 2+5+4 = 11 → 1+1 = 2\n→ NO! Not a multiple of 9.",
      "why_it_works": "This is called the 'divisibility rule for 9'. It works because our base-10 number system has a special relationship with 9 (which is 10-1). Pure mathematical magic!",
      "practice": [
        {
          "q": "Is 243 a multiple of 9?",
          "a": "2+4+3=9 → YES ✓"
        },
        {
          "q": "Is 387 a multiple of 9?",
          "a": "3+8+7=18 → 1+8=9 → YES ✓"
        },
        {
          "q": "Is 456 a multiple of 9?",
          "a": "4+5+6=15 → 1+5=6 → NO ✗"
        },
        {
          "q": "Is 729 a multiple of 9?",
          "a": "7+2+9=18 → 1+8=9 → YES ✓"
        }
