      "example": "6 × 4 = 24 → last digit is 4 ✓\n6 × 8 = 48 → last digit is 8 ✓\n6 × 12 = 72 → last digit is 2 ✓\n6 × 14 = 84 → last digit is 4 ✓\n6 × 16 = 96 → last digit is 6 ✓",
      "why_it_works": "6 × even number always ends in the same digit because 6 = (5+1) and multiplying any even number by 5 gives a number ending in 0, so the +1 just brings back the original ones digit!",
